      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has slightly softened, add the <strong>diced halloumi </strong>and <strong>ras el hanout</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 120ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-high and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until the aubergine has completely softened</p>",
